---
import DocLayout from '@/layouts/DocLayout.astro'
import { productFacts } from '@/lib/facts'
---

<DocLayout
  title="Agents and MCP"
  description="Give an agent a compact local tool surface, deterministic output, and focused instructions without loading every report schema into context."
  section="Automation"
>
  <h2>Use JSON from the CLI</h2>
  <pre><code>seo report --project example --json
seo crawl https://example.com --json --output crawl.json</code></pre>
  <p>
    JSON mode never prompts. Agents should pass explicit selectors, inspect
    data status and caveats, and reuse saved crawl IDs for follow-up questions.
  </p>

  <h2>Install the local MCP server</h2>
  <p>Humans can choose a detected client interactively:</p>
  <pre><code>seo mcp install</code></pre>
  <p>Agents and setup scripts choose the destination explicitly:</p>
  <pre><code>seo mcp install --claude-desktop --json
seo mcp install --claude-code --json
seo mcp install --cursor --json
seo mcp install --all --json</code></pre>
  <p>Run or test the server directly:</p>
  <pre><code>seo mcp serve
seo mcp serve --test</code></pre>

  <h2>Three tools cover the report suite</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Call <code>seo_list_reports</code> to find the smallest relevant report.</li>
    <li>Call <code>seo_describe_report</code> to get that report's input schema.</li>
    <li>Call <code>seo_run_report</code> with the accepted parameters.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    The compact surface keeps dozens of schemas out of the initial context.
    Report results still return structured content and a readable display layer.
  </p>

  <h2>Install focused skills</h2>
  <p>The npm package ships {productFacts.skills} skills:</p>
  <pre><code>seo skills list
seo skills install --target agents
seo skills install --target codex
seo skills install --target claude
seo skills install --target project</code></pre>
  <p>
    Pass a skill name after <code>install</code> to copy one skill, or use
    <code>--dir</code> for a custom skills directory. Add <code>--json</code> in
    unattended setup.
  </p>

  <h2>Reason from evidence</h2>
  <p>
    Check <code>dataStatus</code>, source completeness, row caps, warnings, and
    caveats before reaching a conclusion. Use structured errors instead of
    parsing error text when <code>structuredContent.error</code> is available.
  </p>
</DocLayout>
